The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, June 6: Axis Bank said it would raise Rs 6,520.24 crore in debt through a private placement in Indian or foreign currencies. The board has approved borrowing of up to Rs 6,520.24 crore in one or more tranches by way of upper tier II capital in Indian or foreign currencies and or lower tier II capital in the form of sub-ordinate debenture, Axis bank said in a filing to the BSE.                            
	 New Delhi, June 6: Indiabulls Real Estate has priced the share of its business trust arm at one Singapore dollar, following successful completion of its IPO amid weak market conditions.                             
	 New Delhi, June 6: Clearing the decks for the consolidation of the State Bank of India (SBI), the law ministry has approved the merger of the State Bank of Saurashtra with its parent entity.                             
	 New Delhi, June 6: Bearing the brunt of frequent freight revisions by the railways, the mining industry has sought Prime Minister Manmohan Singhs help in restoring iron ore charges to the level prevailing before 2008 rail budget.                            
	 New Delhi, June 6: The Centre has collected Rs 3,14,468 crore as direct taxes during 2007-08, surpassing the indirect tax mopup by about Rs 34,000 crore for the first time. Direct tax collections grew 36.6 per cent last fiscal.                                                                                                                          
